##What's at stake: APPLE'S SUPPLY CHAIN?

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

Our reporter, Chen Jialan, Chen Yibo, Li Zhenghao, reporting from Beijing and Guangzhou

Every year after the Spring Festival, Liu Wei (not his real name) is at his busiest.

On the afternoon of March 4, Liu Wei, who is familiar with Foxconn's labor supply, told China business daily that "Zhengzhou Foxconn currently employs about 70,000 people at its factories and recruits about 5,000 people a day. " Ten days earlier, on February 24, reporters verified that there were 46 restaurants in Foxconn's Zhengzhou, 24 restaurants opened on the same day, during lunch time a total of 16,423 person-times card records, and another quarantine zone of 6,734 person-times delivery records. Due to the special period of the restaurant cumbersome process, but also a large number of employees choose to solve their own lunch.

However, according to Liu Wei, Foxconn in Zhengzhou is "about 100,000 short" because it normally employs about 150,000 people at its factories, up from a peak of 400,000.

Foxconn in Zhengzhou is the largest contract manufacturer of the IPHONE. Apple CEO Tim Cook. Cook told US media in mid February that foxconn planned to resume 50 per cent of its production in mainland China by the end of February and 80 per cent by March.

But Liu Wei said it was unlikely that Foxconn in Zhengzhou would return to work at 50 per cent by March 4.

In addition, according to Apple's 2019 core supplier list, apple's global suppliers are mainly located in mainland China, Taiwan, the United States, Japan, Europe, South Korea, etc. , other than China, other countries and regions are in the outbreak period, apple's global supply chain whether there is a crisis of concern to the industry.

The assembly plant resumed operation

More than 90 percent of Apple's production capacity comes from the Chinese mainland, according to public data. Foxconn and pegatron make the bulk of the IPHONE. Pegatron refers to Pegatron, whose Shanghai based pegatron technology is the second largest iPhone foundry after Foxconn. FOXCONN's iPhone capacity is concentrated in Zhengzhou (90 per cent) and Shenzhen.

That said, the IPHONE's global supply chain this year will depend first and foremost on the performance of Foxconn and Pegatron, particularly in Zhengzhou.

"Foxconn iDPBG Zhengzhou General Recruitment" official certification official number February 21 push shows that IDPBG (integrated Digital Product Business Group)2-14 levels of employees, if the employee has been on duty before February 29, or is on duty before February 29 but is returning to work, and is on duty before March 18, the employee will be rewarded 3,250 yuan after 60 days and 2,000 yuan after 90 days.

The reporter learned that the salary level of the first-line employees of Foxconn in Zhengzhou is seven thousand RMB, that is to say, as long as the employees who took up their posts at the end of February or mid-march, they can get the same reward as the salary of 1 / 2 to 2 / 3 months.

Zhengzhou Foxconn on the one hand to encourage the old staff to return to work as soon as possible, on the other hand, Labor Service companies are entrusted to "pull people. ". The reporter learned that in mid-to-late February, Foxconn in Zhengzhou continuously increased the incentive policy for labor dispatch companies to "pull people" for it, by the end of February it had become: recruited employees to punch a card for the full 35 days, and in the full 60 days to issue 3300 Yuan Rebate; On this basis, a further payment of 3700 yuan will be made upon completion of 90 days of service.

This is equivalent to the Labor dispatch company for each Zhengzhou Foxconn recruitment of a full 90-day staff, its employees can receive 7,000 yuan (equivalent to foxconn employees'January wages) reward.

Even so, according to Liu Wei, due to the impact of the new crown disease, in February 10 when the resumption of work, at the beginning of the construction of Foxconn in Zhengzhou, "only a few hundred people could be admitted every day. [ apple CEO ] Cook said (50 percent at the end of February and 80 percent in March) that when we were able to admit about 1,000 people every day, now we can admit about 5,000 people every day. At present, the factory has sixty thousand people, but the number of employees in the factory is 100,000 to 150,000, which is the normal level. " Therefore, the current Zhengzhou Foxconn staff gap pressure is still very big.

It is also understood that every year and pegatron and Foxconn in the recruitment of employees will have a war, this year is no exception. The reporter learned that because pegatron's pegatron factory is located in Shanghai, and adjacent to the Hubei Province of Henan, Shanghai epidemic pressure is smaller, so pegatron rehabilitation situation is better. Meanwhile, eager to get to work, it was Chang Shuo who fired the first shot at a high return fee -- a bonus of up to 10,000 yuan for a new employee (90 days in office) .

According to the reporter's investigation, in general, although the iPhone contract factory employment gap is still very big, but in view of the current epidemic situation and the situation of staff recruitment, many industry insiders predict that it is possible to reach 80% of the iPhone contract factory to resume work in March.

Foxconn's parent company said publicly in recent days that at current rates it should be able to return to normal seasonal production by the end of March.

On March 6, Liu Wei told reporters that the first phase of recruitment for Foxconn and pegatron was now basically completed and recruitment pressure had eased, starting with age restrictions.

Apple is also trying to move its assembly business overseas. Apple's China supply chain report, published by The Wall Street Journal on March 3, reveals that as early as 2015, the company's Chief Operating Officer suggested that "at least one product assembly should be transferred to Vietnam. " This allowed apple to conduct "worker training and establish a new system of parts suppliers" outside China, but apple executives refused.

In the middle of last year, it was revealed that apple had asked major suppliers to assess what would happen if it moved 15-30 per cent of its production capacity overseas? Apple's reliance on China's supply chain is unlikely to change for a long time, according to the Wall Street Journal's supply chain report.

Supply chain concerns

While Foxconn and pegatron are under pressure to return to production, apple's global supply chain, which is in charge of the "feed" , is also in dire straits. Perhaps more worrying than Chinese suppliers are apple suppliers in Europe, Japan and South Korea.

According to South Korean media reports, Samsung Electronics in the southeastern city of Gumi (Gumi) since February 21, the first case of a new crown confirmed cases, to March 2, there have been four cases, leading to the factory production line has been closed several times. In addition, LG Display, the main Display unit of LG, as well as the main camera-providing LG Innotek also affected by the outbreak of work stoppage.

Samsung and LG suppliers in mainland China, senior told reporters that the current epidemic prevention measures in South Korea is to stop production of cases, full disinfection disinfection, two or three days after the resumption of production. The problem is that at factories like Samsung's turtle tail, where one case comes in every few days and requires constant shutdowns, the impact is still huge.

According to Apple's 200 core suppliers list for 2019, its suppliers are 41 in mainland China, 46 in Taiwan, 38 in the United States, 38 in Japan, 18 in Europe and 11 in South Korea. These countries and regions are basically epidemic. In South Korea, for example, Samsung Electronics and Samsung Sdi in the Samsung Galaxy, as well as LG Display and LG LG chem in the LG Galaxy, are apple's core suppliers. Stmicroelectronics, based in Italy, one of the hardest hit areas in Europe, is also a concern in apple's supply chain.

Apple's key suppliers in Shandong Province are mainly in Shandong and overseas, with 50,000 workers in Shandong and 10,000 in overseas factories, executives told reporters on March 4. At present, Shandong factory to the post is the main staff of the province, most of the provincial staff has not been able to return to work, the overall rate of less than 70% . Chinese workers at overseas factories also have to be quarantined for 14 days to get to work.

The most challenging part of Apple's current supply chain is the fact that its assembly plants are not fully operational, and as an accessory supplier, you can see the order data from the assembly plants constantly fluctuating, the executive said, but so far there is no so-called "haggling" behavior, the supply chain is still in operation as planned.

Liu Wei told reporters that apple upstream supplier companies are also extremely short of people, according to his understanding, like Kecheng, Kecheng enterprises, a labor supplier to send dozens of people a day. "He is a total of more than a dozen labor suppliers in a factory area. On average, he sends dozens of people to each factory, which is too few, " Li Chengwei, an independent observer of the Labor Industry and the founder of the Labor Teahouse, told reporters, compared to previous years when no one was around after the 15th of the first month, this year's post-holiday labor service is a protracted battle, enterprises are expected to continue until around the end of March, early April to complete the recruitment.

A source close to Lens Technology, another of Apple's key suppliers in China, told reporters that the company's order book is so full that it has doubled its demand for human resources compared with previous years -- it is likely to require 100,000 people in Florida, however, at present, the staff on duty can meet the existing capacity demand, and the staff recruitment for the new capacity demand in the new park is being intensified.

Lens provides the glass back cover for the IPHONE. After the Spring Festival, Liu Wei said, rance technology is not a high-priced employer, but rance technology is eager to recruit people. Recently, local governments have gone to the village to "recruit people" for the rance technology factory in Changsha, Hunan Province. Lens Technology confirmed that the local government help into the village recruitment is indeed the case.

With the new crown epidemic spreading around the world, could there be a crisis at some key points in apple's global supply chain? According to an analysis by the Shandong supplier executive, there are two to three suppliers in every link of Apple's supply chain. The share of the first two suppliers will reach 80% to 90% , and the share of the third supplier will generally be less than 10% , if one of the suppliers in one segment has a problem, one or two others should step in; even if all the suppliers in one segment have a problem, there will be a "safety stock" to help cushion it, so it won't be a big problem in the short term.

Lv Junkuan, research director of Gartner, also told reporters that the impact of the global epidemic on Apple's supply chain "can be covered, and in reality there are a lot of control methods to get [ parts ] supply and [ assembly plants ] back to normal. ".

Lv Junkuan also mentioned that apple supply chain every link "still have some inventory, " together with the resumption of the supply chain and follow-up work, the progress should be able to catch up.

Demand side changes are more important

The global impact of the current crown disease on Apple's supply chain is clear. On this point, Cook admitted at the February 27 meeting that there are "challenges" ahead. But from the survey, the industry generally believed that the "factory of the world" China is speeding up the resumption of production from the epidemic, from a year-round view of the impact is manageable.

For example, Lu said in an interview that the production and supply of existing models of the iPhone was "I feel OK" , "But new products such as the new iPhone S1, which was supposed to go on sale, have not been released and there is no certainty of when it will go on sale, so it has an impact on the new product. " On the other hand, Lu said, "The launch of new products [ every year ] in September is not likely to have an impact, but supply could be affected and there could be a shortage. "

For the smartphone industry, the good news is that the second half of the year is usually a busy one, and the year-round impact is unlikely to be significant from that perspective, according to the Shandong supplier executive.

Li Zhijia, an Hui investment fund manager, also believes that, the new crown "definitely has an impact, but it's not going to be fatal right now, because the existing models are available and there are no new products. If the outbreak happens in September or November, the impact on apple will be huge. ".

Lu also warned that global demand for smartphones may be more of a concern than supply of parts and assembly plants.

"I think the supply chain problems are minor and the impact of the epidemic on the global economy is the big problem. Supply chain problems will only have a small impact on apple's short-term profitability, but not on the global economy,"he said, "It now looks like if the epidemics in countries like Italy and Iran continue, [ the epidemic ] will have a global impact on the demand side, not just on the Chinese market. "In addition, the epidemic in the US is rising rapidly, and there is an impact on consumer purchases on the demand side. "

"As long as demand doesn't disappear, [ Apple's supply chain ] can catch up to a certain extent through follow-up work, " an electronics analyst at a domestic brokerage also told reporters

The analyst also said the drop in demand for smartphones in the first quarter of this year would not be too small from the Chinese market's point of view, and that "if the epidemic in China is brought under control by the end of April, the situation could improve a lot in the second quarter" . Globally, expectations are currently mixed, with "some arguing that a 10 per cent adjustment is already large, others that a 15 per cent adjustment is likely to be small" .

In addition, the impact of the outbreak on global capital markets, including U. S. stocks, is deepening. Since Feb. 20, Apple's stock has fallen nearly 10 percent from a volatile $323.62 to $292.92 at the close on March 5, according to the data Apple's market value fell by $0.2 trillion, from $1.4 trillion on Feb. 19 to $1.2 trillion on March 5.

In response, Zhang He, a partner in investment management and a senior visiting scholar at Columbia University, Gao Guolei, said, regarding the issue of the decline in Apple's share price, "The first thing to see is that the continuous decline in the U.S. stock market is now widespread, and it's not just apple's problem. At the same time, this is an election year in the United States, and there has been a lot of volatility in the stock market for almost every election year in history, because a new president is often a little more different in style than his predecessor."

As far as apple's fundamentals are concerned, Gao Guolai believes that the factors that can have an impact on apple's future performance mainly include: First, the uncertainty of the global epidemic, and its impact on the supply and demand side of apple products; Second, the growth rate and revenue share of Apple's services revenue are continuing to rise, which is good for apple if this segment continues to perform well. Third, the growth rate of apple's hardware revenue has indeed slowed in the last two years, but the total number of users is still rising, if the total amount of stagflation is bad for Apple's future performance.
